Information and Communication Engineering Department Homepage Renewal

Our team's project goal is to renew the design of the department's homepage and add a chatbot function to reorganize it to make it easier to obtain user experience and information


# Information and Communication Engineering Department Homepage Renewal

## ðŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project aims to **renew the official homepage** of the Department of Information and Communication Engineering. Our primary goal is to enhance the **user experience (UX)** and **information accessibility** by modernizing the overall design and integrating a **smart chatbot feature**.

Through this project, we intend to transform the existing site into a more **user-friendly**, **visually engaging**, and **functional** platform for students, faculty, and visitors.

## ðŸŽ¯ Project Objectives

- Redesign the homepage with a modern and responsive layout.
- Improve accessibility and navigation structure for better usability.
- Add a chatbot assistant to help users:
  - Easily obtain academic information
  - Get answers to FAQs
  - Navigate the website through natural interaction
- Optimize the website for both desktop and mobile users.
- Improve overall load speed and performance.

## âœ¨ Key Features

- **Responsive Web Design**: Supports both desktop and mobile browsers.
- **Chatbot Integration**: Powered by a simple NLP-based assistant (RAG, or custom model).
- **User-Centered Navigation**: Clear and intuitive UI for quick access to content like curriculum, faculty info, and announcements.
- **Admin-Friendly Update System**: Structure for easier content management in the future.
- **Multilingual Support** *(optional)*: English/Korean toggle to accommodate diverse users.

## ðŸ›  Technologies & Tools

- **Frontend**: HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, React.js, TailwindCSS
- **Backend**: Node.js / Express (or Python Flask)
- **Chatbot**: Python (RAG-based local model)
- **Version Control**: Git, GitHub
- **Design**: Adobe


